reviews.text: My wife and I got the burrito‚Äôs. They were delicious and very filling. Thank you for the great service.

I moved here 2017.. im not fast foid eater..buy this surpass fast food. Love the giant burritos great fast lunch & filling n it just enough for lunch.  Love the tacos n burritos bowls. This is family owned business.. very crowded at times and always polite fun atmosphere w a friend.  The staff& service always fast &  on point perfection orders filled.  No mistakes ever.  My favorite lunch quick spot.  I go at least once a week. Thank Taco Dog.
I had a bowl here and it was great, but I definitely think it should've been more portions. Outside of that everything  was cool.

2 visits so far and I‚Äôve tried multiple items from the menu. The best thing on the menu are the corndogs. I tried the chili dogs. I didn‚Äôt notice the chili whatsoever as if it was nonexistent. The steak quesadilla was flavorless. But I came back the second time for the corndogs. Service is good, but the restaurant is not kept clean as the pictures will show. I noticed that the food is set waiting directly next to the cash register so while your food is being prepared other customers are standing over your food while they pay for theirs.

The guacamole though...whoo!!  So good and fresh.  The whole family loves the corn dogs, extra large with a sweet batter...yummy!  Employees are always courteous; having fun and getting the job done, even when the place is poppin'!!

editorial_summary.overview: Colorful counter-serve cafe offering Tex-Mex tacos & burritos, plus a unique selection of hot dogs.

detailedReviews.author: Timothy Evanchick
detailedReviews.text:
Possibly the most pretentious (and worst) chilli chese dog Ive ever had. Its like they sprinkled cheese on a hot dog and microwaved it in an effort to be more "gormet". This place is absolutely the kind of place where "foodies" go to pay more for worse food while feeling better than other people because they have "refined tastes" even when it comes to casual affair.  The owner is a nice guy but he makes a hot dog like someone who has never seen one AND makes them NY, CA, Chicaco, etc... style all while seemingly never set foot in those places.

As a New Yorker, if you want a NY style hot dog, you boil it in dirty water, reach into the bun bag with hands you havent washed in days, and place it on the tray, wipe your nose on your shirt, reach into the water with the tongs you just dropped on the ground, and place the dog on the bun. Hand it to the customer with the option for them to squirt some store bought ketchup/mustard on it and you've done your job. Maybe they have a nice meal, maybe they contract typhoid. Its the gamble we play on the streets of NY when partaking in street meat. But you know what those vendors have that this restaraunt doesnt? A good hotdog.

detailedReviews.text: The name Taco "Dog" fits this place. They charge $4.25 for a Taco "Grande" which is one single sloppy made Taco, served in a plastic basket. Expensive dog food!

detailedReviews.author: Tricia Jones
detailedReviews.text: Went for the first time today and while the food was good, it was a hair overpriced for what it was. However the worst part came when my fiance and I were leaving, he told me that while waiting to use the bathroom he heard an employee use the restroom and promptly leave without washing their hands. When I asked if he was sure, he said yes bc the paper towel dispenser makes noise when you use it and the sink was dry when he went in after them. Really unfortunate because otherwise we might have been back, but questioning the sanitation now so it's a no for us.

detailedReviews.author: KB
detailedReviews.text: Got cheeseburgers Togo tonight. The customer service was off the chart! The phone call making the order, the guy was repeating my requests to make sure it was delivered correctly. When I arrived I was greeted with friendly faces. I believe I spoke to the owner or manager who came out to ask how I was doing today. I also over heard this person coaching and complimenting some of the employees, I really was impressed. I got a small town family restaurant vibe here. It was my first visit but not my last! The food tasted great! French fries tasted good with no sauce. Thank you for a great experience, the extra mile given doesn‚Äôt go unnoticed.

Response to the owner:
If the drink was added to the Cheeseburger price, then I was double charged because the Coke on the receipt is what I drank and was charged for. Feel free to drink one on me today.
